history.content:
If your goal is to take CS 189 in the spring, then I would recommend just taking CS 188, CS 170, and EE 127.

EE 126 is not directly as relevant to 189, its more just good for building mathematical maturity and practice with probability and inference. You can probably self-study the relevant portions of probability for 189 (probability basics, distributions, information theory, multivariate gaussians, and statistical inference). EE 126 goes into depth on many topics like stochastic processes, random graphs, kalman filtering, etc. that are really cool topics in their own regard but not that relevant for 189 directly. 

EE 127 on the other hand is much more directly related to 189, all the linear algebra, vector calculus, and mathematical optimization stuff from 127 comes back in full force in 189.

children.subject: OP here. The only reason I'm hesitant to take 126 is that it's in-person and is late in the evening. So would taking 127+170+188 in the fall and then 189+126 in the spring be a good plan?
127 + 189 is better concurrently, I would swap 127 and 126
If you take 127, is it still necessary to take math 53 before CS 189?

I would disagree with the student answer, I found 126 very useful for building more probability maturity I didn't really get fully from 70. If you feel really comfortable with probability content I suppose you could afford to skip it, but I wouldn't recommend.

127 is also useful, although in my experience didn't do all that great a job of teaching vector calculus. A lot of the linear algebra concepts are already touched on in 16ab as well, although they do a better job teaching it than 16ab imo. I took 127 concurrently with 189, and I found this perfect: I didn't feel like I necessarily needed what I learned in 127 to succeed in 189, but it was really interesting content to learn in relation to 189.

I would also add that 188 really isn't important for 189 at all (they give a very light treatment of machine learning but I find it hard to see as really preparing you for 189). It's a great class to take still, but not as a prerequisite for 189.

I'd encourage you to either consider 126 + 127 + 170 and then 189 + 188 in the spring, or 126 + 188 + 170 and then 189 + 127 in the spring.
